  "text": "Marketing of urban places has been practiced since the nineteenth century [CITATION_1] ; however, studies on destination image as a concept of branding theory began in the early Hunt's (1975) influential work on the relationship between image and tourism development. The theoretical emergence of place marketing was accelerated by three developments in the marketing discipline: marketing in non-profit organizations, social marketing, and image marketing [CITATION_2] .",
